Keras is a high-level neural networking library written in Python. It was developed with a focus on enabling rapid prototyping, allowing users to create models efficiently with minimal code. Keras runs on top of TensorFlow, Theano, or Pocket PyTorch, and can be described as a user-friendly, modular, and easy-to-extend neural network framework that supports both convolutional networks (used mainly for image processing) and recurrent networks (suitable for sequential data like text, time series, or speech).
